This paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The problem of minimizing energy consumption is also relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as energy-efficient computing is an important consideration in these fields. Finally, the use of preemption and migration of jobs suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant.
